---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  pageHeading="Join the Network"
  description="How I got my first Meshtastic node running. Takes about 45 minutes and $50."
>
  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">
      Getting your first node running
    </h2>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      This took me about 45 minutes total. Most of that was waiting for Amazon delivery.
    </p>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      If you can pair Bluetooth headphones and follow five steps, you can do this.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- The Honest Motivation -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-prairie-gold/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-prairie-gold/5 to-sunset-amber/5 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-prairie-gold/20 dark:from-prairie-gold/10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Why you might want to do this</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        <strong>Emergency backup communications.</strong> When cell towers are down, this keeps working. Some people care a lot about that. It's a real use case.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Off-grid messaging.</strong> Camping, events, rural areas with spotty service—it works anywhere.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Honestly? It's just fun.</strong> Building infrastructure with cheap radios is cool. Watching messages hop across the city on hardware you deployed is satisfying. That's why I'm doing this.
      </p>
      <p>
        Whatever your reason—practical or just because it's interesting—here's how to get started.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 1: Get Hardware -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Step 1: Get hardware</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        You need a LoRa radio that runs Meshtastic. I started with a Heltec LoRa32 V3 ($25-30 on Amazon). Worked fine.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>If you just want to try this:</strong> Get the cheapest compatible device. Heltec V3 or similar. Under $35.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>If you want GPS and mobile use:</strong> Get a LILYGO T-Beam (~$40-50). Has GPS built in, better for portable/vehicle use.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Budget Option: Heltec V3</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $25-30</p>
          <p><strong>Pros:</strong> Cheap, proven, has screen</p>
          <p><strong>Cons:</strong> No GPS, basic antenna</p>
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Testing, indoor use, budget entry</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-ink-600 dark:text-cream-200">This is what I started with. Got me on the mesh for under $30.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Better Option: T-Beam</h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $40-50</p>
          <p><strong>Pros:</strong> GPS included, good battery life</p>
          <p><strong>Cons:</strong> $20 more than basic</p>
          <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Mobile use, position tracking</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-ink-600 dark:text-cream-200">This is what I'd buy if I were starting over.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl bg-kc-blue/5 border border-kc-blue/20 p-5 dark:bg-kc-sky/5 dark:border-kc-sky/20">
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <strong>Where to buy:</strong> Amazon (fast, easy returns) or AliExpress (cheaper, slower). Make sure it's 915 MHz (US frequency) and ESP32-based.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      <a href="/get-started/hardware" class="text-base font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
        See full hardware guide with specific links →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 2: Install App -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Step 2: Install the Meshtastic app</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        While you're waiting for hardware to arrive, install the app on your phone.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">iOS</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Search "Meshtastic" in the App Store. Free. Works on iOS 14+.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Android</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Search "Meshtastic" in Google Play. Free. Works on Android 8+.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 3: Configure -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Step 3: Configure your node</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        Device arrived? Good. Plug it into USB power (phone charger, computer, power bank—doesn't matter). Wait about 30 seconds for it to boot.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Here's what confused me at first:</strong> The device creates its own Bluetooth connection. You're not connecting it to WiFi. You're pairing your phone to the device via Bluetooth, then using the app to configure it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
      <details class="group rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">1. Pair with your phone</summary>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p>Open the Meshtastic app. Tap the "+" button. Select your device from the list.</p>
          <p>It might ask for a PIN. Usually "123456" or shown on the device screen.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">2. Set your node name</summary>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p>I use "KC-YourName" format. Like "KC-Jeremy" or "KC-Brookside-1".</p>
          <p>Makes it easy to identify Kansas City nodes. Use whatever makes sense to you.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">3. Select region</summary>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>This is critical:</strong> Choose "United States" (sets 915 MHz).</p>
          <p>Wrong region = wrong frequency = you won't connect to anyone.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">4. Set location (optional but helpful)</summary>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p>If your device has GPS, it'll set this automatically. If not, you can manually enter your general area.</p>
          <p>Helps with network planning. You can approximate (within a mile) if you want privacy.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">5. Join the default channel</summary>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p>Use the "LongFast" preset. This is the main KC mesh channel.</p>
          <p>Don't mess with settings unless you know why. Defaults work.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 4: See Who's Out There -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Step 4: See who's out there</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        <strong>If you see "0 nodes online" — that's normal if you're the first in your area.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        Your node is still working. It's just not seeing anyone else yet. As more people join, that number grows. This is how mesh networks start—one node at a time.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you're within range of Router 1 (east side KC), you should see it within a few minutes. Check the coverage map to see if you're in range.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl bg-mesh-green/10 border border-mesh-green/30 p-5">
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <strong>You can send messages even if you see 0 nodes.</strong> They'll store-and-forward when someone comes in range. That's how mesh works.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Next -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">What next?</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Test range</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Move your node to different locations. Window vs. outdoor. Higher elevation gets better range. Test and see what works for your building.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Consider upgrades</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Better antenna ($20-40) dramatically improves range. Solar power (~$50-100) enables permanent outdoor deployment. But start basic, optimize later.
        </p>
        <a href="/guides/solar-residential" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
          Solar setup guide →
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Spread the word</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Mesh works better with more participants. Tell friends, neighbors, anyone interested in backup comms or cool radio tech.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- You're Done -->
  <section class="mt-12 text-center">
    <div class="inline-block rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue to-kc-red p-8 text-cream-50 shadow-card md:p-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">That's it. You're on the mesh.</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-base opacity-95">
        Wasn't that hard, right? Now you've got backup communications that work when cell towers don't.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a
          href="/network/coverage"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cream-50 px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue transition hover:bg-surface-200"
        >
          Check Coverage Map
        </a>
        <a
          href="/community/contact"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-cream-50 px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-cream-50 transition hover:bg-cream-50 hover:text-kc-blue"
        >
          Questions? Contact Me
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
